    "toc": [
      {
        "label": "\n        What is Life? The Physical Aspect of the Living Cell\n      ",
        "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0001.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "\n        Foreword\n      ",
        "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0011.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "\n        Preface\n      ",
        "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0002.xhtml",
        "subitems": []
      },
      {
        "label": "\n        1. The general Character and the Purpose of the Investigation\n      ",
        "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0003.xhtml",
        "subitems": [
          {
            "label": "\n          Statistical Physics. The Fundamental Difference in Structure\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0003.xhtml#heading_id_3",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The Naïve Physicist's Approach to the Subject\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0003.xhtml#heading_id_4",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Why Are the Atoms so Small?\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0003.xhtml#heading_id_5",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The Working of an Organism Requires Exact Physical Laws\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0003.xhtml#heading_id_6",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Physical Laws Rest on Atomic Statistics and Are Therefore Only Approximate\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0003.xhtml#heading_id_7",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Their Precision Is Based on the Large Number of Atoms Intervening. First Example (Paramagnetism)\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0003.xhtml#heading_id_8",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Second Example (Brownian Movement, Diffusion).\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0003.xhtml#heading_id_9",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Third Example (Limits of Accuracy of Measuring)\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0003.xhtml#heading_id_10",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The √n Rule\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0003.xhtml#heading_id_11",
            "subitems": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "label": "\n        2. The Hereditary Mechanism\n      ",
        "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml",
        "subitems": [
          {
            "label": "\n          The Classical Physicist's Expectation, Far from Being Trivial, Is Wrong\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_3",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The Hereditary Code-Script (Chromosomes)\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_4",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          How do the chromosomes behave in ontogenesis?\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_5",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          In Mitosis Every Chromosome Is Duplicated\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_6",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Reductive Division (Meiosis) and Fertilization (Syngamy)\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_7",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Haploid Individuals\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_8",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The Outstanding Relevance of the Reductive Division\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_9",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Crossing-Over. Location of Properties\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_10",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Maximum Size of a Gene\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_11",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Small Numbers\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_12",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Permanence\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0004.xhtml#heading_id_13",
            "subitems": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "label": "\n        3. Mutations\n      ",
        "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml",
        "subitems": [
          {
            "label": "\n          'Jump-Like' Mutations The Working-Ground of Natural Selection\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml#heading_id_3",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          They Breed True, That Is, They Are Perfectly Inherited\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml#heading_id_4",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Localization. Recessivity and Dominance\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml#heading_id_5",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Introducing Some Technical Language\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml#heading_id_6",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The Harmful Effect of Close-Breeding\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml#heading_id_7",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          General and Historical Remarks.\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml#heading_id_8",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The Necessity of Mutation Being a Rare Event\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml#heading_id_9",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Mutations Induced by X-Rays\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml#heading_id_10",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          First Law. Mutation Is a Single Event\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml#heading_id_11",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Second Law. Localization of the Event\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0005.xhtml#heading_id_12",
            "subitems": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "label": "\n        4. The Quantum-Mechanical Evidence\n      ",
        "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0006.xhtml",
        "subitems": [
          {
            "label": "\n          Permanence Unexplainable by Classical Physics\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0006.xhtml#heading_id_3",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Explicable by Quantum Theory.\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0006.xhtml#heading_id_4",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Quantum Theory, Discrete States, Quantum Jumps\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0006.xhtml#heading_id_5",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Molecules\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0006.xhtml#heading_id_6",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Their Stability Dependent on Temperature\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0006.xhtml#heading_id_7",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Mathematical Interlude\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0006.xhtml#heading_id_8",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          First Amendment\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0006.xhtml#heading_id_9",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Second Amendment\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0006.xhtml#heading_id_10",
            "subitems": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "label": "\n        5. Delbrück's Model Discussed and Tested\n      ",
        "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml",
        "subitems": [
          {
            "label": "\n          The General Picture of the Hereditary Substance\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_3",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The Uniqueness of the Picture\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_4",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Some Traditional Misconceptions\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_5",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Different 'States' of Matter\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_6",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The Aperiodic Solid\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_7",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The Variety of Contents Compressed in the Miniature Code.\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_8",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Stability of Naturally Selected Genes\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_9",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          The Sometimes Lower Stability of Mutants\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_10",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Temperature Influences Unstable Genes Less Than Stable Ones\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_11",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          How X-Rays Produce Mutation\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_12",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Their Efficiency Does Not Depend on Spontaneous Mutability\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_13",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Reversible Mutations.\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0007.xhtml#heading_id_14",
            "subitems": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "label": "\n        6. Order, Disorder and Entropy\n      ",
        "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0008_split_000.xhtml",
        "subitems": [
          {
            "label": "\n          A Remarkable General Conclusion from the Model\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0008_split_000.xhtml#heading_id_3",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Order Based on Order\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0008_split_000.xhtml#heading_id_4",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Living Matter Evades the Decay to Equilibrium\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0008_split_000.xhtml#heading_id_5",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          It Feeds on 'Negative Entropy'\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0008_split_000.xhtml#heading_id_6",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          What Is Entropy?\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0008_split_000.xhtml#heading_id_7",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Organization Maintained by Extracting 'Order' from the Environment\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0008_split_000.xhtml#heading_id_8",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Note to Chapter 6\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0008_split_001.xhtml",
            "subitems": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "label": "\n        7. Is Life Based on the Laws of Physics?\n      ",
        "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0009.xhtml",
        "subitems": [
          {
            "label": "\n          New Laws to Be Expected in the Organism\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0009.xhtml#heading_id_3",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Reviewing the Biological Situation\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0009.xhtml#heading_id_4",
            "subitems": []
          },
          {
            "label": "\n          Summarizing the Physical Situation\n        ",
            "href": "OEBPS/Text/Section0009.xhtml#heading_id_5",
            "subitems": []
          },
